.Dd May 17, 2026
.Dt DOOMSDAY-SYSTEM 1
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm doomsday-system
.Nd install the DOOMSDAY X11 desktop modules
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm install.sh
.Op Ar module
.Op Ar option ...
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm
is a meta-installer for a small X11 desktop stack. It clones selected module
repositories, builds the C tools, and installs dotfiles through their own
Makefile.
.Pp
With no module flag, the installer defaults to
.Fl -all .
.Sh MODULES
.Bl -tag -width "--slstatus"
.It Fl -dots
Install DoomDots.
.It Fl -wm
Install VeryDynamicWindowManager and DoomMenu.
.It Fl -sst
Install StealthStreamTerminal.
.It Fl -slstatus
Install SentinelStatus.
.It Fl -slock
Install ShadowLock.
.It Fl -all
Install every module.
.El
.Sh OPTIONS
.Bl -tag -width "--dotfiles-prefix DIR"
.It Fl y , Fl -yes
Run non-interactively.
.It Fl -dry-run
Print planned actions without changing the system.
.It Fl -list
List modules and exit.
.It Fl -uninstall
Uninstall selected modules instead of installing them.
.It Fl -no-verify
Skip post-install command verification.
.It Fl -no-deps
Skip package-manager dependency installation.
.It Fl -no-update
Do not update existing module checkouts.
.It Fl -build-root Ar DIR
Clone and build modules under
.Ar DIR .
.It Fl -prefix Ar DIR
Install compiled tools under
.Ar DIR .
.It Fl -dotfiles-prefix Ar DIR
Install dotfile symlinks under
.Ar DIR .
.It Fl -repo-base Ar URL
Use a different GitHub or Git-compatible repository base URL.
.El
.Sh EXAMPLES
.Dl \&./install.sh --dry-run --all
.Dl \&./install.sh --yes --wm --sst
.Dl \&./install.sh --uninstall --slock
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr doomdots 1 ,
.Xr verydynamicwindowmanager 1 ,
.Xr doommenu 1 ,
.Xr stealthstreamterminal 1 ,
.Xr sentinelstatus 1 ,
.Xr shadowlock 1
